This paper is primarily focused on instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed methods involve the use of fully convolutional neural networks (FCN), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the advantages of its approach in terms of transparency and simplicity, which are topics that are often discussed in the neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) subcategories.
